.TH setupterm 3
.SH NAME
\*Lsetupterm\*O \- Performs low level terminal setup
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O

\*Lsetupterm(\*Vterm\*L, \*Vfilenum\*L, \*Verrret\*L)
    char *\*Vterm\*L;
    int \*Vfilenum\*L;
    int *\*Verrret\*L;\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "setupterm subroutine"
This function sets up the terminal from the \*Lterminfo\*O
database.  The parameter \*Lterm\*O is the terminal type.
If this parameter is set to \*LNULL\*O, the environment variable
\*LTERM\*O will be used. The \*Lfilenum\*O parameter is a
file descriptor, not a \*Lstdio\*O pointer.
It is used for all the output generated by \*Lsetupterm\*O.
.PP
The \*Lterminfo\*O boolean, numeric, and string values
are stored in a structure of type \*LTERMINAL\*O.
.PP
After \*Lsetupterm\*O returns successfully the variable
\*Lcur_term\*O is initialized.  This variable points to the
\*LTERMINAL\*O structure.  The \*Lcur_term\*O
pointer can be saved before calling \*Lsetupterm\*O
again as further calls to \*Lsetupterm\*O allocate new space;
the space pointed to by \*Lcur_term\*O is not overwritten.
